  --- JTA ached data.</li>   <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">xa</code>   Use this mode when you cache data from other data stores (eg: DBMS, JMS) and want to do it in an atomic way under the control of the JTA API but don’t want to pay the price of full two-phase commit. In this mode, your cached data can get out of sync with the other resources participating in the transactions in case of a crash so only use it if you can afford to live with stale data for a brief period of time.</li>   <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">xa_strict</code>   Same as xa but use it only if you need strict XA disaster recovery guarantees. In this mode, the cached data can never get out of sync with the other resource
